						               													<description>Murder mystery party game for 8-12 players that you host at home. Each player dresses up as a character, one is the murderer and the rest must figure out who that is. To solve the mystery there are clues, police report, crime scene photos, and a map. You go over these materials then question all the players about what their characters did and saw to finally solve who done it. The game lasts a times 2.5 hours.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Remember the excitement and glamour of your Senior Prom? Well now you can relive it, 1980s style. McKinley High School is having their Senior Prom, and like your typical prom there will be punch, snacks, a student rock band, and the coronation of the prom king and queen.&amp;#10;This could be any American population, with the in-crowd, jocks, geeks, dopers, losers, and even the well liked, super cool drug dealer. Don&amp;rsquo;t you remember how fun it all was?&amp;#10;On this particular prom night though there is more going on than your standard spiked punch and necking in a dark corner. Real murder and mayhem is brewing. By the end of the night you will be shocked and astonished and will have lost a considerable amount of respect for your fellow students and the school faculty (who would have thought!).&amp;#10;So throw on a boutonniere, squeeze into that tiny gown, fluff your hair up big and get ready to boogey on down with some punch, canapes, cookies, and some drop dead entertainment.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
